data.enText: to make sb decide not to do sth or continue doing sth, especially by making them understand the difficulties and unpleasant results of their actions

data.chText: 我已告诉他我不感兴趣，可他却不罢休。
data.enText: I told him I wasn't interested, but he wasn't deterred.

data.chText: 这么高的服务费可能使咨询者望而却步。
data.enText: The high price of the service could deter people from seeking advice.

simple_means.memory_skill: de 使… + ter〔= terr〕怕；恐吓 → 恐吓 → 阻止

example: Negative campaigning will only dissuade people
We should discourage this practice among our youth

value.def: To deter someone from doing something means to make them not want to do it or continue doing it.

example.ex: Supporters of the death penalty argue that it would deter criminals from carrying guns...
example.tran: 死刑的支持者认为它能阻吓罪犯携带枪支。

example.ex: Arrests and jail sentences have done nothing to deter the protesters...
example.tran: 逮捕和监禁都没能吓倒抗议者。

example.ex: Jeremy was not deterred by this criticism.
example.tran: 杰里米没有因这一批评而却步。
